The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 November is 96,817 (11,158.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 November, there were 4,752 new confirmed cases (547.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 October, there were 4,498 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 6% (254 extra cases).
